Redis Kya Hai?

Redis (Remote Dictionary Server) ek in-memory NoSQL database hai.

Iska matlab:

Data RAM me store hota hai (Hard Disk me nahi).
Isliye ye MongoDB se bahut fast hota hai.
Redis ko mostly temporary data store karne ke liye use kiya jata hai.

Ek line definition (README ke liye):

Redis is an in-memory key-value database used for high-speed caching, session management, OTP storage, rate limiting, and message queuing.

1. Cache
Problem

Suppose tumhari website par 10,000 users hain.

Har baar user profile kholte hi:

User
   ↓
Node.js
   ↓
MongoDB

Har request MongoDB tak jayegi.

MongoDB slow ho jayegi.

Solution

Pehli baar MongoDB se data lao.

Uske baad Redis me save kar do.

User
   ↓
Node.js
   ↓
Redis ✅
   ↓
MongoDB (sirf first time)

Agle users ko Redis se data milega.

Redis RAM me hota hai isliye milliseconds me response deta hai.

Example:

GET /profile

MongoDB

300ms

Redis

5ms
2. OTP Store

OTP permanent data nahi hota.

Suppose:

OTP = 483921

Ye sirf

5 minutes

tak valid hai.

MongoDB me rakhna waste hai.

Redis me aise store karte hain:

Key

otp:9876543210

Value

483921

Expiry

300 sec

5 minute baad Redis khud delete kar deta hai.

Is feature ko kehte hain

TTL (Time To Live)

Isliye authentication apps Redis use karti hain.

3. Session Storage

Suppose user login karta hai.

Email
Password

Verify ho gaya.

Ab har request pe password thodi bhejega.

Server ek Session banata hai.

Session ID

abc123xyz

Redis me save hota hai.

abc123xyz

↓

User ID = 10

Ab jab bhi request aayegi

Cookie

abc123xyz

Redis se user identify ho jayega.

Redis fast hai isliye login system bhi fast hota hai.

4. Authentication

Authentication matlab

"Ye banda kaun hai?"

Example

Login

Redis authentication me directly use nahi hota.

Lekin support karta hai:

OTP
Session
Token blacklist
Refresh token

Example:

JWT Logout

JWT normally expire hone tak valid rehta hai.

Logout ke baad Redis me blacklist kar dete hain.

Blacklisted Token

abc.def.xyz

Agar dubara aaye

Reject
5. Rate Limiting

Suppose koi hacker login API ko hit kar raha hai.

POST /login

10000 times.

Server crash ho jayega.

Redis har IP ka counter rakhta hai.

IP

192.168.1.10

↓

Count = 15

Rule

10 requests/minute

11th request

429 Too Many Requests

Ye brute-force attacks aur API abuse rokne ke liye use hota hai.

6. Message Queue

Suppose user register hua.

Uske baad

Welcome Email
SMS
Notification

sab bhejna hai.

Agar sab immediately karoge

Register

↓

Email

↓

SMS

↓

Notification

API slow ho jayegi.

Instead

Register

↓

Redis Queue

↓

Worker

↓

Email

User ko response turant mil jata hai.

Background worker baad me email bhej deta hai.

Ye asynchronous processing kehlata hai.

BullMQ Redis ke upar bana hua ek job queue (message queue) library hai jo Node.js me background tasks handle karne ke liye use hota hai.

Simple language me:

Redis = Queue ko store karta hai.
BullMQ = Queue ko manage karta hai (jobs add karna, process karna, retry karna, scheduling, etc.).

Real-life Example

Suppose user ne signup kiya.

Agar tum signup ke baad email bhi turant bhejoge:

User Signup
      ↓
Save User
      ↓
Send Email
      ↓
Return Response

Agar email service slow hui to user ko bhi wait karna padega.

BullMQ ke saath
User Signup
      ↓
Save User
      ↓
Add Email Job to BullMQ
      ↓
Return Response ✅ (Fast)

Background Worker
      ↓
Reads Job from Redis
      ↓
Sends Email

User ko response instantly mil jata hai, aur email background me chali jati hai.

BullMQ ka flow
Client
   ↓
Node.js API
   ↓
BullMQ Queue
   ↓
Redis
   ↓
Worker
   ↓
Email / SMS / Notification / Image Processing
BullMQ kis-kis kaam me use hota hai?
📧 Send Emails
📱 Send SMS
🔔 Push Notifications
🖼️ Image Processing
🎥 Video Processing
📄 PDF Generation
📊 Report Generation
⏰ Scheduled Jobs (Cron Jobs)
🔄 Retry Failed Jobs

Redis vs BullMQ
Redis	BullMQ
In-memory database	Job Queue Library
Data store karta hai	Jobs manage karta hai
Queue ko save karta hai	Queue create aur process karta hai
Standalone database	Redis ke bina nahi chal sakta

Redis ko kyun use karte hain?
Feature	MongoDB	Redis
Data Store	Disk	RAM
Speed	Fast	Extremely Fast
Permanent Data	✅	❌ (Usually Temporary)
Cache	❌	✅
OTP	❌	✅
Session	❌	✅
Rate Limiting	❌	✅
Message Queue	❌	✅
Interview Definition (1-2 lines)

Redis:

Redis is a high-performance in-memory key-value database used to store temporary data for fast access.

Caching:

Storing frequently accessed data in Redis to reduce database queries and improve response time.

OTP Store:

Storing OTPs with an expiry time (TTL) so they are automatically deleted after they expire.

Session Storage:

Keeping user session data in Redis for fast authentication and scalable login management.

Authentication:

Verifying a user's identity. Redis commonly supports authentication by storing sessions, refresh tokens, OTPs, or token blacklists.

Rate Limiting:

Restricting the number of requests a client can make within a specific time period to prevent abuse and brute-force attacks.

Message Queue:

Temporarily storing tasks (such as sending emails or notifications) so background workers can process them asynchronously without delaying the user's request.